column5: Great fish and very cool video. You're so calm and collected except for that angry growl at the 1:18 mark.

One more pic from another follow on the figure 8 it stuck to the lure for about 3 figure 8's but then left bad part is in the video my arm blocks most of the video Oh well its still cool when I get it done here is a shot of it any way
Ron dont tell her my tape starts at 4"  Mike I had to laugh at my self also I knew she was pulling alot but did not know I had to get hulk out to help get her from under the boat
Very cool Mike.  Good job on getting it up loaded.

That one was almost easy Brian it's the next that are getting fun mixing all the shots together I have it almost done kinda there all uploaded or downloaded to my Mac just need to get them all into one.

Well today was supposed to be my first day back to work after my holidays I show up at 6am and am told they did not have me scheduled for a run so before they could find something I was out the door (actually they gave my run to some one else Oh well)  Anyway I turned that into a positive and went home hooked up the boat and headed to LSC plan was do some more casting for slime it worked out great I boated 3 had 7 other miss hits and follows I only took one picture she was a beauty 50 1/2" one of the others was mid 30's and the other around 40's it was a great day now I just need some pointers on how to get my video from the gopro to my Mac? I have tried but it seems to be taking for ever each video is about 3-8min long.  Any help on this one?  here are a couple pics until I figure this video thing out
That is a great day of work Mike  That is a beautiful beast right there, look at the tongue on it
Wow. I need (must!) try Muskie fishing sometime.
I'd call that a good day at the office.  Way to go Mike!
Well done Mike! I might try to get out Saturday depending on when I get back Friday. Sunday morning is out, dropping the girls off at the airport but maybe an afternoon fish is in order.
Big chomper on the beast!
Beats work any day Mike, well done.  I can imbed the video for you if you PM me a link to it.
nice fish
Some people have all the luck.  Sounds like a real good day on the water Mike. Nice fish.

Very smart move getting out of there before they found something for you  !  What probs are you having downloading your video ? An 8 minute video shouldn't take very long to download at all.  Give me a holler if you need any more help.
Nice pics thanks.  Watch were you put your thumb they like white meat.

Well I got one of the many videos on the mac now but I dont have a clue what Im doing to crop it down I have it down to 1min 24 sec but when I try to save it I can not Im using I movie and have about wore my brain out dang I owe alot to the guys who make these videos look so awesome. I have alot of footage from today I just want to make a small video of it all or at least the big girl and a couple boat strikes. I did figure out how to get a picture from it so here are 4 from her jump boat side.
Nice action pics!   Same here.
Very nice Mike, do you get a run tomorrow? That will help buy more lures:lol:. Good luck with the new job!!
Nice going Mike !!!Wish i had work days like that:thumbsup_anim:
Now THIS I want to see as video Mike ! Quicktime is a good way to resize videos for the web.
Nice stuff Mr Parker!!!
After your 8 plus hour return drive to Cameron, i knew good Kharma would come your way, well done Mike, thats 2 50s in a week out of your boat
I think I got it done this time here is the first video I just need to work on piecing the others together from the follows and splashes and then try and get some music to go with the other video
nice job on the fish and vids mike! I can come over and give ya a few pointers on imovie sometime!
That would be great Ron I know you guys do some great vids. When are you heading east for the season?
Way to go Mike !!  That's a beauty.  Congrats on a great day.  Gonna be making a couple of trips down your way this fall.  I'll give you a heads up when I'm coming.
Jim please do we will have done BBQ and chat if there is time after fishing. Bring your casting gear and your best boat partner.
Nice vid Mike and even a greater fish! Geesh, go figure eh..... A half inch bigger than your wifes..... HA HA HA LMAO.  Good on ya bud.  Cheers, Ron...
